# Linux Fundamentals Part 3 Write-Up

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ Deploying the Linux Machine / AttackBox
# Start your Linux machine and AttackBox (IP: 10.201.3.195, User: tryhackme, Password: tryhackme).

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ Nano (Text Editor)
# Create/edit files: nano myfile
# Save: Ctrl+O ‚Üí Exit: Ctrl+X
# Useful shortcuts: Ctrl+W (search), Ctrl+_ (go to line), Ctrl+K/U (cut/paste)

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ VIM (Advanced Editor)
# Open file: vim myfile
# Features: syntax highlighting, custom shortcuts, works on all terminals

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ Downloading Files (wget)
# Download a file from the web: wget <url>

# 5Ô∏è‚É£ Transferring Files (SCP)
# Local ‚Üí Remote: scp important.txt ubuntu@192.168.1.30:/home/ubuntu/transferred.txt
# Remote ‚Üí Local: scp ubuntu@192.168.1.30:/home/ubuntu/documents.txt notes.txt

# 6Ô∏è‚É£ Serving Files (Python HTTPServer)
# Start server: python3 -m http.server
# Download file: wget http://<host-ip>:8000/myfile
# Stop server: Ctrl+C

# 7Ô∏è‚É£ Processes
# List processes: ps aux, top
# Kill process: kill <PID> (SIGTERM, SIGKILL, SIGSTOP)
# Background process: command &
# Pause process: Ctrl+Z
# Foreground: fg

# 8Ô∏è‚É£ Crontabs (Automation)
# Edit crontab: crontab -e
# Example: 0 5 * * 1 tar -zcf /var/backups/home.tgz /home/
# Run script on boot: @reboot /var/opt/processes.sh

# 9Ô∏è‚É£ Package Management & Repositories
# Add GPG key: wget -qO - https://download.sublimetext.com/sublimehq-pub.gpg | sudo apt-key add -
# Add repository: echo "deb https://download.sublimetext.com/ apt/stable/" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/sublime-text.list
# Update apt & install: sudo apt update && sudo apt install sublime-text
# Remove repo: sudo add-apt-repository --remove ppa:PPA_Name/ppa
# Remove package: sudo apt remove sublime-text

# üîü Logs
# Apache logs: sudo cat /var/log/apache2/access.log
# Get visitor IP: sudo tail -n 1 /var/log/apache2/access.log | awk '{print $1}'
# Monitor fail2ban/UFW logs in /var/log/

# ‚úÖ Summary
# This module covered terminal editors, downloading/serving files, process management, crontabs, package management, and log monitoring.
